[DhtmlXQ_comment0]smg 20120919 What would you do if you were GM Yang part 3c||||In Sept 1977, the Chinese National Singles Xiangqi preliminaries were held.||GM Yang Guanlin took red and started the game with the elephant opening. His opponent was  Shi Juemin ??? from Inner Mongolia, who countered Yang's elephant opening with the Left Central Cannon Counter.||A simple analysis of the game shows that all the major pieces are intact and red is only one pawn down. Red's left chariot and cannon have already been pushed deep into enemy territory and the two horses on the riverbank are threatening.||We start at move 17, GM Yang's turn... ||What would you do if you were GM Yang?[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]By sacrificing the cannon, GM Yang tempts black's chariot to leave its current position, thereby allowing his horses to attack.||The depth and precision of his calculations are astounding! ||This move can be thought as a flying dagger, piercing black's heart..[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
[DhtmlXQ_comment2]Click on the variations to see what might have happened if black refused the exchange...[/DhtmlXQ_comment2]
