[DhtmlXQ_comment13]Another sacrifice!!!||Red sacrifices three major pieces! ||GM Yang knows after analysis, that his remaining forces on the board are more than enough for a blistering kill.[/DhtmlXQ_comment13]
[DhtmlXQ_comment16]In his haste, black played this move, thus losing his chariot.||R4-2 would have prevented the loss of this chariot and would enable black to hold on a little bit longer![/DhtmlXQ_comment16]
[DhtmlXQ_comment31]Red wins.||In this example, GM Yang (red) his chess pieces in superior positions, all poised to attack. However, black still has a stubborn defence.||GM Yang starts with a cannon sacrifice to break open black's defense. He then tempts the black chariots away from defensive positions to start his vicious attack, and after a few more sacrifices, he manages to get the win![/DhtmlXQ_comment31]
